 # Replace shell-interpolated run() with execFileSync to prevent metacharacter breakage
 
-
+All run() call sites in storage-backend.ts build shell command strings via template literal interpolation. Paths, branch names, repo URLs, and commit messages are injected unescaped. A task title like 'Fix the "login" flow (1/2)' would produce broken shell quoting.
+
+Fix: replace execSync with execFileSync and pass arguments as an array:
+  function run(args: readonly string[], cwd: string): void {
+    execFileSync(args[0]!, args.slice(1), { cwd, stdio: 'pipe' });
+  }
+
+Call sites become: run(['jj', 'commit', '-m', message], workspacePath)
+
+This is a mechanical but broad refactor — every run() call site in storage-backend.ts needs updating. Do as a dedicated commit.
+
